(c)2011, cFrames

BRIEF:
cFrames is a model/view/controller framework designed to provide optimal perfomance while keeping ease of development at a minimum. The cFrames program is implemented using C++ and .e files are interpreted by the program to build a web application. 

STRUCTURE:

ROOT - app    - controllers
     |        | models
     |        | views      - layouts      
     | db     - 
     | config - 
     | tmp    -
     | log    -

